div.p:
The Powers have from time to time stationed armed forces, including
                                police and railway guards, in China to protect the lives and
                                property of foreigners lawfully in China;

To the end that there may be clear understanding of the conditions
                                upon which in each case the practical execution of those intentions
                                must depend;

And whereas the continued maintenance of
                                these forces appears to be mainly responsible for China’s present
                                unsettled political conditions;
